1. Difference between jar/war/ear files
JAR- (JAVA Archive)
     Jar file is a collection of .class files.
     JAR files are used in J2EE for packaging EJBs and client-side Java Applications.
WAR- (WEB Archive)
     War file holds all web application related components like servlets,jsps,html pages,css, etc..
     1 war file for each web application.
EAR - (Enterprice Archive)
     EAR holds all JAVA related components used for enterprise applications.
     (.jar and .war) are packaged as JAR file with .ear (enterprise archive) extension and deployed into Application Server.
